Description: Two fragments of blank papyrus. P BM EA 10382.10 and 10382.11 are numbered together as 10382.10 in Thompson's MS Catalogue. For the photograph, see entry for P BM EA 10382.10. Thompson's MS Catalogue (concerning all fragments P BM EA 10382 [he lists 10 of them]): "not mounted, kept in portfolio in 10 sheets of paper. apparently disconnected documents & fragments, but all of c. Persian period (BC. 525-332)".
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (381181) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/381181)
